docs.abstract: The Senate approved a Middle East policy bill that rebukes President Trump’s troop withdrawals while backing Israel against a movement to boycott it.
docs.snippet: The Senate approved a Middle East policy bill that rebukes President Trump’s troop withdrawals while backing Israel against a movement to boycott it.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate overwhelmingly approved a Middle East policy bill on Tuesday that included both a rebuke to President Trump over his withdrawal of troops from Syria and Afghanistan and a contested measure to allow state and municipal governments to punish companies that boycott, divest from or place sanctions on Israel.

headline.main: Senate Passes Bill That Rebukes Trump and Opposes Israel Boycott
headline.print_headline: Senate Passes Bill That Rebukes President and Opposes a Boycott of Israel

docs.abstract: The American and North Korean leaders are expected to hold their second summit meeting on Feb. 27 and 28.
docs.snippet: The American and North Korean leaders are expected to hold their second summit meeting on Feb. 27 and 28.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump announced on Tuesday that he will sit down with North Korea’s leader, Kim Jong-un, at the end of this month in Vietnam, a country chosen as a neutral location for their second nuclear summit meeting, but one that also has plenty of symbolic significance.

headline.main: Trump to Meet With Kim Jong-un in Vietnam
headline.print_headline: Trump to Meet With Kim In Vietnam This Month

docs.abstract: In Idaho and Utah, two conservative states, voters approved initiatives to expand Medicaid under the Affordable Care Act. Now G.O.P. lawmakers are looking to curb those expansions.
docs.snippet: In Idaho and Utah, two conservative states, voters approved initiatives to expand Medicaid under the Affordable Care Act. Now G.O.P. lawmakers are looking to curb those expansions.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The voters of Utah and Idaho, two deeply Republican states, defied the will of their political leaders in November and voted to expand Medicaid under the Affordable Care Act. Now those leaders are striking back, moving to roll back the expansions — with encouragement, they say, from the Trump administration.

headline.main: In Utah and Idaho, G.O.P. Looks to Curb Medicaid Expansions That Voters Approved
headline.print_headline: G.O.P. Looks to Cut Medicaid Expansions

docs.abstract: The Postal Service blamed “human error” for the release of a Democratic House candidate’s security clearance application, requesting that a Republican super PAC return it.
docs.snippet: The Postal Service blamed “human error” for the release of a Democratic House candidate’s security clearance application, requesting that a Republican super PAC return it.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Postal Service said on Thursday that it “deeply regrets our mistake in inappropriately releasing” the official personnel file of Abigail Spanberger, a former C.I.A. operative now running as a Democratic candidate for Congress, and requested that a Republican-aligned super PAC return the documents.

headline.main: Postal Service Improperly Divulged Spanberger’s Sensitive National Security File, and Asks for It Back
headline.print_headline: Apology, but Few Details, From the Postal Service Over a File’s Disclosure

docs.abstract: Representative Andy Barr defeated his well-financed Democratic challenger, Amy McGrath, on Tuesday, buoying Republican hopes of minimizing their losses.
docs.snippet: Representative Andy Barr defeated his well-financed Democratic challenger, Amy McGrath, on Tuesday, buoying Republican hopes of minimizing their losses.
docs.lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Ky. — Representative Andy Barr, an incumbent Republican, defeated one of the Democratic Party’s most prominent challengers, Amy McGrath, on Tuesday in a deeply conservative district here, according to The Associated Press, giving his party hope of limiting losses in the race for control of the House.

headline.main: Andy Barr Defeats Amy McGrath in Kentucky House Race, Buoying Republican Hopes

docs.abstract: With the government shutdown nearing the end of its third week, the president also suggested that he might declare a national emergency to bypass Congress.
docs.snippet: With the government shutdown nearing the end of its third week, the president also suggested that he might declare a national emergency to bypass Congress.
docs.lead_paragraph: McALLEN, Tex. — President Trump arrived in this border town Thursday on a trip that he did not want to take to discuss a crisis that Democrats say does not exist, repeating his request for a long-promised border wall that has led to a bitter political impasse and a 20-day government shutdown.

headline.main: Trump, Along the Border in Texas, Reiterates Demand for Wall

byline.original: By Michael Tackett and Katie Rogers

docs.abstract: Ms. McGrath, a retired Marine combat aviator, was supposed to be the Democrat who could bridge the urban-rural chasm. But her loss in a Kentucky congressional race exemplifies the nation’s divide.
docs.snippet: Ms. McGrath, a retired Marine combat aviator, was supposed to be the Democrat who could bridge the urban-rural chasm. But her loss in a Kentucky congressional race exemplifies the nation’s divide.
docs.lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Ky. — At 5 a.m. on Election Day, Mark Nickolas awoke to write a speech he thought would never be delivered.

headline.main: Amy McGrath, a Soaring Democratic Candidate, Is Brought Back to Earth on Election Day
headline.print_headline: Urban-Rural Divide Was Too Much for Rising Kentucky Democrat to Bridge

docs.abstract: But in McAllen, where crime is near a 30-year low, there seemed to be a different reality.
docs.snippet: But in McAllen, where crime is near a 30-year low, there seemed to be a different reality.
docs.lead_paragraph: McALLEN, Tex. — When a president comes to town there are two realities, the one the White House hopes to create and the one that actually exists.

headline.main: In Texas Visit, Trump Presses His Argument That There’s a Border ‘Crisis’

docs.abstract: In Mr. Mulvaney, President Trump chose a hard-line conservative and former congressman with a deep understanding of how Congress works and a personal chemistry with Mr. Trump.
docs.snippet: In Mr. Mulvaney, President Trump chose a hard-line conservative and former congressman with a deep understanding of how Congress works and a personal chemistry with Mr. Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump announced on Friday that he had selected Mick Mulvaney, his budget director, to serve as acting White House chief of staff, putting a halt — at least for now — to his consideration of a parade of possible candidates, including several who turned him down, to take over one of the most important positions in the federal government.

headline.main: Trump Names Mick Mulvaney Acting Chief of Staff
headline.print_headline: Trump Picks Budget Chief To Lead Staff

docs.abstract: President Trump reprised his use of a movie-style poster at a Cabinet meeting. But he let the prop speak for itself.
docs.snippet: President Trump reprised his use of a movie-style poster at a Cabinet meeting. But he let the prop speak for itself.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As political props go, the one in the middle of the conference table during President Trump’s cabinet meeting on Wednesday was as hard to miss as it was baffling.

headline.main: A ‘Game of Thrones’-Style Poster Overshadowed a Trump Cabinet Meeting. Nobody Talked About It.
